result.name: Arashigawa Yakitori

reviews.text: Tapas-like skewers, really nice place, good prices

Lunch set is a good deal and very tasty – you get grilled meat or fish, rice, miso and pickled vegetable sides for like $60 HKD. I've been here for that multiple times. Dinner options are much more costly.
Overall, above average. Love the angus beef and lamb. Everything else is pleasant but forgettable.
A local Japanese restaurant serving Japanese yakitori.
The lunch set is great. Decent value and tastes good. The dinner is a bit pricey tho with only skewers available.

result.name: Tapaella Grill

reviews.text:
Nice food and service. Set lunch is very value for money.  

Date of visit: 24 July 2019

Set lunch is decent and not expensive and the pasta dishes are delicious.  Highly recommend seafood pasta, protion is big, and lots of seafood in it.  So yummy....  Their lunch is served with salad or soup, coffee or dessert.  We have chosen ham salad, they use jamon as ham, impressive.

Only there is room of improvement is the aircon, every time when we dine there, we feel hot, especially when it is full house, it is indeed stuffy.
Very good seafood try the seafood paella and pil pil prawns
great food. good value
Good value, old school. Reasonably authentic Spanish. Great service. Very healthy sized glasses of wine!
